The War-Hound Wakes.

SCENE 1: THE WAR-HOUND WAKES

Location: The Riften canal / market level, right as the party climbs out of the
Ratway. Time: Late afternoon/early evening. The Cast: The Party, Esbern, Mila,
and Bjorn.

THE EMERGENCE (Read Aloud)

"You climb the damp stone stairs out of the Ratway, the heavy iron grate
clanging shut behind you. The crisp autumn air of Riften hits your lungs—a
jarring contrast to the blood, stagnant water, and fear you left below.

Esbern is blinking rapidly, adjusting to the daylight he hasn't seen in thirty
years. Mila is clutching Saijah’s hand with a death grip, her enormous eyes
darting around the open sky and the towering wooden structures of the city.
She’s terrified, but she’s walking forward.

A few yards away, near the canal bridge, the cart is parked. Bjorn is brushing
down Mable’s coat. He hears the grate close and turns around, a smile starting
to form on his face at the sight of you.

Then, his eyes drop to Saijah’s side. He sees Mila.

The brush slips out of Bjorn's hand. It hits the cobblestones.

For the first time since you have known him, the jovial, tired old carter
vanishes. His posture changes. His shoulders square. The deep, warm lines around
his eyes pull taut into a mask of absolute, chilling stillness. The air around
him suddenly feels very heavy.

He walks toward you. He isn't shuffling. He moves with a liquid, terrifying
grace that belongs to a much younger, much deadlier man. He stops six feet away,
his eyes locked on the little girl, and when he speaks, his voice is low, raspy,
and stripped of all warmth."

Bjorn: "Whose child is that."

THE CONFESSION & THE ERUPTION

Let Saijah or Alfonso explain. Let them say they saved her, or that they bought
her for 100 gold because her mother was trading her for skooma. Let them try to
frame it as a rescue.

Bjorn listens in dead silence. Then, the dam breaks.

Bjorn (to the party): "You bought her? Like a sack of grain? Like a new sword?
You think you saved her?"

(He points a finger at Davinia, his voice rising, raw with fury) "Look at
yourselves! Look at what you are! You are hunted by the Thalmor! You are
tracking Dragon Priests! You sleep in the dirt, you bleed every day, and half of
you aren't even human anymore!"

(He rounds on Saijah and Alfonso) "You didn't save her from the dark. You just
dragged her into the center of the apocalypse! What are you going to do when a
dragon breathes fire on the cart? What are you going to do when a Justiciar puts
a blade to her throat to make you drop your weapons? Who feeds her when you're
underground fighting walking corpses?"

THE INTERVENTION (The Protective Instinct)

If a player gets defensive or tries to argue that she's safer with them than in
a skooma den:

Bjorn: "Safe?! There is no 'safe' within fifty miles of you! I have seen what
happens when children get caught in the wake of people like us! They don't get
adventures. They get butchered."

He doesn't wait for permission. He steps forward and drops to one knee in front
of Mila, bringing himself down to her eye level. The terrifying intensity drops
instantly, replaced by a fierce, desperate gentleness.

Bjorn (to Mila): "What's your name, little one?" (Mila whispers her name).
"Mila. I'm Bjorn. You're going to come sit on the cart with me, alright?"

He gently takes her hand from Saijah. (GM Note: Do not make this a physical
struggle. If Saijah resists, Bjorn looks up at her with eyes that promise
absolute violence if she doesn't let go).

he leads her to the cart then walks back over to the lanterns.

He doesn't wait for them to argue. He points a heavy, calloused finger back
toward the center of the city.

Bjorn: "There is an orphanage three streets over. Honorhall. It's safe. It has
walls, beds, and a headmistress the whole city loves. We take her there, we give
the woman a bag of gold to make sure she's fed, and we walk away before whatever
is hunting us catches up."

The Collision (Orion & Saijah's Move)

This is where the party has to stop him. Orion knows (from the dead drop or the
Thieves Guild) that Honorhall is a torture factory run by Grelod. Saijah, with
her new predator senses, might have even heard the muted, terrified heartbeats
of the children inside when they walked past it earlier.

Let the party intervene. Let Orion or Saijah tell Bjorn what Honorhall actually
is—that handing her to Grelod is handing her to a monster who breaks kids to
feed the Thieves Guild.

The Realization (Bjorn's Trauma)

Bjorn listens to them explain what the orphanage really is. Watch his face fall.
The anger drains out of him, replaced by a cold, crushing horror.

He remembers the two girls he tried to save forty years ago. He thought they
would be safe on the road with him, but a wealthy, "civilized" noble took them
and skinned them alive behind the closed doors of a fine estate.

Now, he's being told that the "safe, civilized" orphanage in Riften is just
another slaughterhouse run by a respected monster.

He realizes there is nowhere safe to leave her. Not the sewers. Not her mother.
Not the orphanage. And not the open road.

THE VOW (Clean Script)

Bjorn looks back at Mila. The explosive anger drains out of him, leaving a
fierce, weary resignation.

Bjorn (to Mila): "I'm sorry. I thought there was a safe place for you here."

He stands up, facing Davinia, Alfonso, Saijah, and Orion. His shoulders settle
under the heavy weight of his years. He meets your gazes with eyes that are
incredibly old and infinitely tired.

Bjorn: "You're right. We can't leave her here. But she is a child. She stays on
the cart with me. You keep her out of your fights. You keep her out of the
shadows."

He takes a slow, ragged breath.

Bjorn: ""I stayed with you all because I believed you were better than the
monsters I used to hunt. But if you let the darkness you carry spill over and
catch her in the crossfire... I will pack the cart, take her, and leave. And I
won't ever come back. Are we clear?"


